{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1783127697,"nonce":"5yIaoMFVYyS+pNsryr7bpZZbHrA=","message":"PR 4b merged (#73, squash b3d5178): SQLite incremental plan rendering (render_plan) — the last core piece of the backend.\n\n- Native ALTER for changes SQLite supports in place (add/drop/rename column, rename table, create/drop/alter index); a 12-step create-copy-drop-rename table REBUILD for everything else (column type change, and add/drop/alter of primary key / unique / foreign key / check, all inline-only in SQLite). The rebuild copies surviving data (mapping renamed columns and applying cast-column conversions), preserves rows even when every column is replaced (via an unshadowed rowid alias), carries the AUTOINCREMENT high-water mark, and recreates the target's indexes.\n- Core seam: render_plan / render_plan_concurrent + the render_plan_sql / render_plan_with_options / apply_plan / apply_plan_with_options helpers now take the target DatabaseModel (a rebuild needs the full table, incl. unchanged columns, which the per-change plan steps do not carry); PG/MySQL ignore it. New SchemaBackend::supports_concurrent_index_creation (default false; PG true) gates the concurrent-index split so SQLite applies plans transactionally. DatabaseModel gains Default.\n- Executor: execute_ddl applies a plan with a foreign-key envelope — enforcement disabled outside the transaction (a rebuild's DROP TABLE would otherwise cascade-delete children), PRAGMA foreign_key_check before commit, and the prior foreign_keys setting restored afterwards.\n- Table/index names share SQLite's one namespace: all dropped names are freed up front so moves/swaps and name reuse across tables/indexes apply correctly; the target namespace is validated as create-from-scratch does.\n- 23 in-memory plan tests (rebuild data preservation incl. ON DELETE CASCADE children, churn convergence, cast conversions, rowid shadowing, index/table name reuse, FK-check rejection). Codex: 8 rounds, all findings (AUTOINCREMENT high-water, index idempotency/namespace, cast expressions, comment churn, row loss, rowid shadowing, foreign_keys restore) fixed and verified; clean pass.\n\nDeferred: table CHECK constraints and column collations (rejected for now — not introspectable without CREATE TABLE-text parsing); SQLite views (git-bug 39f4468).","files":null}]}